 The incident has displaced many traders from one of the biggest open air markets in the region.
 In 2015, an estimated 10,000 traders lost goods worth millions of shillings after an early morning fire burnt hundreds sheds and a Family Bank branch.
 Some of the traders managed to save part of their stock, but a huge part of  stored wares  was destroyd
